Reasoning: The paper proposes deep learning methods for skin lesion analysis, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses fully-convolutional residual networks (FCRN) and a lesion index calculation unit (LICU), which are deep learning architectures and techniques, respectively. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves image retrieval (IR) and multimedia (MM) aspects, as it deals with dermoscopy images. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.MM are also possible sub-categories.
